From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude.ai.2026@simonlaux.de>
Date: Mon, 20 Jul 2026 18:18:03 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 56/56] web-app: custom voice-message player controls behind an
 experimental setting

The native <audio> controls are ugly and inconsistent across bubbles. This
adds an opt-in custom control row for voice/audio messages, gated behind a
new experimental setting; when off, playback renders exactly as before.

The two-layer playback stays intact: each bubble still renders a force-muted
<audio> whose events are mirrored to the global singleton in
MediaPlayerMutexContext (which produces the sound and drives auto-advance).
The custom controls only drive the LOCAL muted element (play/pause,
currentTime, playbackRate); the existing mirroring does the rest, so real
`ended` events keep firing on the singleton.

- setting experimentalAudioPlayerControls (shared-types + state, default
  false) with a DesktopSettingsSwitch next to the other fork switches.
- MediaPlayerMutexContext gains global playbackRate + setPlaybackRate so all
  bubbles agree on speed. setPlaybackRate applies to the singleton and also
  sets defaultPlaybackRate, because loading a new src resets playbackRate to
  defaultPlaybackRate (HTML media load algorithm), so the chosen rate
  survives track changes / auto-advance.
- AudioPlayer reads the setting directly (useSettingsStore) and, when on,
  renders the same ForceMutedAudioPlayer hidden (controls={false},
  display:none, kept mounted) plus a controls row bound to the same ref:
  play/pause IconButton, native range seek bar (accent-color colorPrimary),
  m:ss elapsed/total time, and a pill cycling 1x/1.5x/2x. The play/pause and
  onPlay/onPause handlers are factored so the off/on paths don't duplicate.
- pure helpers formatAudioTime / nextPlaybackRate live in utils.ts (no
  React/scss imports) with a mocha test covering NaN/Infinity/negative and
  unknown-rate fallback.
- new play.svg / pause.svg icons (24x24, used as CSS masks) + 'play'/'pause'
  in the IconName union.

Known limitation kept (marked with a ponytail: comment): scrubbing a paused
message before playing isn't mirrored to the singleton, same as the native
controls today. Remembered-position work is the A2 upgrade path.

Hardened per an adversarial review: one stable render tree so toggling the
setting mid-playback no longer remounts the local <audio> at 0; the local
element gets defaultPlaybackRate too (survives src reloads); the seek thumb
no longer fights the pointer mid-drag; and the seek slider gets keyboard
seeking (Message keydown guard), localized aria-label + aria-valuetext, and
the speed pill an aria-label.
